<!-- Start Body -->
I never, ever drink coffee, tea, coca-cola or any other caffeine containing drinks.  I don't like thermally hot drinks and can't stand the taste of coke.  So I could be classed as a caffeine virgin.  Occasionally (once or twice a year?) I would have a cup of black coffee to help me study all night...  It always made me feel pretty rotten.<BR>
<BR>
One Christmas when I was around 17 I got a bag of chocolate covered coffee bean sweets. They were pretty nice.  Very nice in fact and I kept dipping into them.  By the time it was go to to bed I'd had the whole bag of them. Not an inconsiderable amount - in fact I would estimate it was the equivalent of over 15 cups of coffee.  I had no intention at all of getting high, in fact this never crossed my mind.  However, when I got to bed I could not sleep at all.  I was incredibly restless, I had terrible sweats and my mind was racing.  I felt sick.  I probably got to sleep at about 4 am.  I am still off the coffee and this wasn't an experience I want to repeat but thought it was worth reporting to show how potent caffeine can be.<!-- End Body -->
<br/><br style="clear:both;"/>


